item.name: Bloc by Bloc: The Insurrection Game
Blood on the Clocktower
item.comment:
Originally played this game a year and a half ago at Origins Game Fair (2018). It was a very late night, and the first play I went in to, I had no sweet clue what was happening. It wasn't well explained, and I also wasn't grasping the concepts behind the game.
Fast forward to March 2019, and I have played the game over 70 times. I host Clocktower gameplay in Toronto, Canada, bi-weekly for an insatiable crowd of people that are part of the Toronto Wolf'd (werewolf) group. We love it, and some hate it and still keep coming back for more. Weird, eh?
Good times.

item.name: A Fake Artist Goes to New York
Faza
item.comment:
First play, 4 people. Really enjoyed. The game beats you up—and that was on normal mode, standard setup.
Some of my friends didn't enjoy the art style, or the colouring, but as someone who works in the art direction/design field, I found it exceptional. Perhaps bumping up the paint colours for the orange drones might help, but everything else was excellent IMO.
This game is a keeper—and I am not one for cooperative games. You know, I keep saying that, but when I play them, I actually enjoy them. Not all, but games like Horrified, Spirit Island, and now this, are on the keeper list. This and Horrified are tied for ease-of-play and willingness to come out to the table any time.

item.comment: First play was 2-person. Tight game. Second play was with 4 people. The point system is solid. Very tight race. Final scoring really brings the game to life for a fantastic finish. 4 player game was difficult at times to keep track of what to do, as your turn happens once every 4 times—someone could potentially ruin your strategy. But that's gaming. I enjoy this game and am glad I have it in my collection.

item.comment: Yup. Beautiful and clever. Build paths, score points based on how many "passes" over tiles you make. Points are equal to the height (or level) of each tile you pass through. So I think the third game and onward will be far more rewarding when playing.
